<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-660-391  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 660 391.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Nov 26 1990 n618 p48(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>On to a successful transition. (to a peace-based electronicsindustry) (part of a special section comprising ElectronicEngineering Times' annual report on the military segment of theelectronics market)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Iverson, J.R.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The American Electronics Association has examined the issuesfacing the defense electronics industry in the changing politicaland economic climate of the 1990s and has arrived at a number ofrecommendations for actions on the part of government and on thepart of industry.andP;  The principles underlying the recommendationsinclude the creation of a radically different defense procurementsystem, more cooperation between government and industry, and abilateral approach to formulating procurement rules andregulations.andP;  Among the recommended steps for government areencouraging a shift to awarding contracts on the basis of bestvalue, as opposed to the traditional lowest bidder focus,encouraging research and development by allowing commercializationof results, and expanding efforts to relieve export restrictions.andO;Recommendations for industry include targeting the $245 billionannual market for high-tech currently filled by imports,capitalizing on research in defense technology by turning it tocommercial applications, and seeking opportunities in dual-usetechnologies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MilitaryElectronic IndustryAnalysisGuidelinesAmerican Electronics Association.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>